# Content inventory (auto-update)

The repo tracks every MkDocs nav page in `content-inventory.csv` and `content-inventory.md` (6 columns: title, content status, en/fa/zh complete, human review).

## When this rule applies

Run the generator after **any** change that can affect the inventory:

- Edit `mkdocs.yml` nav (add / remove / rename / reorder pages)
- Add, remove, or rename a `.md` page linked from nav
- Add or update locale variants (`.fa.md`, `.zh.md`)
- Change `scripts/content-review.yaml` (human-review flags)
- Run doc generators that create or sync markdown (`generate-config-guide.py`, `sync-i18n-pages.py`, etc.)

## Required step before finishing

Always run:

```bash
python3 scripts/generate-content-inventory.py
```

When adding or renaming nav pages, also pass `--sync-review` so new entries land in `scripts/data/content-review.yaml`.

Also regenerate the live-site trust UI:

```bash
python3 scripts/generate-page-trust-manifest.py
```

This command:

1. Scans all nav entries in `mkdocs.yml`
2. Writes `content-inventory.csv` and `content-inventory.md`
3. With `--sync-review`: appends **new** pages to `scripts/data/content-review.yaml` with `reviewed: false`

## Include in the same change set

When the user asks for a commit, stage together:

- The doc / nav change
- `reports/content-inventory.csv`
- `reports/content-inventory.md`
- `scripts/data/content-review.yaml` (if new pages were appended)

Do **not** hand-edit the CSV or markdown table — regenerate instead.

## Human review column

- Set `reviewed: true` (or per-locale `en` / `fa` / `zh`) in `scripts/data/content-review.yaml`, then re-run the generator.
- Pages not listed show **Unknown**; auto-added pages show **No** until reviewed.

## CI

Pull requests fail if inventory files are stale. If CI reports an out-of-date inventory, run the command above and commit the outputs.
